cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it addresses the problem of semantic correspondence between images. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of synthetic geometric deformations and the differentiable version of the argmax function may suggest that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) categories.
